The species name “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Salani &amp; Willenz &amp; Fernandez &amp; Hajdu" authorityYear="2022" box="[559,652,331,356]" class="Demospongiae" family="Hymedesmiidae" genus="Hymedesmia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="6" pageNumber="223" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="peruana">
<emphasis box="[559,652,331,356]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="223">peruana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” is used as a noun in apposition that refers to 
<collectingCountry box="[1170,1225,331,357]" name="Peru" pageId="6" pageNumber="223">Peru</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
