<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="223" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1677,1920]" pageId="6" pageNumber="223">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1678,1704]" pageId="6" pageNumber="223">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Salani &amp; Willenz &amp; Fernandez &amp; Hajdu, 2022" authorityName="Salani &amp; Willenz &amp; Fernandez &amp; Hajdu" authorityYear="2022" box="[323,621,1677,1704]" class="Demospongiae" family="Hymedesmiidae" genus="Hymedesmia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="6" pageNumber="217" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="peruana" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Hymedesmia">
<emphasis box="[323,468,1677,1703]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="223">Hymedesmia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[484,504,1678,1703]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="223">H</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[528,621,1678,1703]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="223">peruana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[629,719,1678,1704]" pageId="6" pageNumber="223">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[629,719,1678,1704]" pageId="6" pageNumber="223" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Salani &amp; Willenz &amp; Fernandez &amp; Hajdu, 2022" authorityName="Salani &amp; Willenz &amp; Fernandez &amp; Hajdu" authorityYear="2022" box="[868,1093,1678,1704]" class="Demospongiae" family="Hymedesmiidae" genus="Hymedesmia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="santarositae" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Hymedesmia">
<emphasis box="[868,888,1678,1703]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="223">H</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[912,932,1678,1703]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="223">H</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[956,1093,1678,1703]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="223">santarositae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1101,1191,1678,1704]" pageId="6" pageNumber="223">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1101,1191,1678,1704]" pageId="6" pageNumber="223" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, by the combined absence of sigmas and microstrongyles (
<tableCitation box="[576,659,1713,1740]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="8.[151,239,612,638]" captionText="TABLE 1. Hymedesmia (Hymedesmia) spp. from Peru. Measurements (in µm) of the spicules (n = 30; unless stated otherwise in parentheses), length x thickness [as minimum– mean–maximum (± standard deviation)], distribution and bathymetry (in meters). Roman numerals correspond to size categories of acanthostyles.Abbreviations: Tor. (tornotes), Str. (strongyles), Sbty. (subtylotes), Tyl. (tyles), Sty. (styles), Ac. (arcuate chelae), Sig. (sigmas) and Mstr. (microstrongyles)." pageId="6" pageNumber="223">Table 1</tableCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="Goodwin et al., 2012" authorityName="Goodwin" authorityYear="2012" box="[683,1219,1713,1740]" class="Demospongiae" family="Hymedesmiidae" genus="Hymedesmia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="6" pageNumber="223" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="croftsae" subGenus="Hymedesmia">
<emphasis box="[683,828,1713,1739]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="223">Hymedesmia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[844,872,1714,1739]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="223">H.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[887,976,1713,1739]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="223">croftsae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Goodwin, C. &amp; Brewin, P. E. &amp; Brickle, P." box="[983,1219,1713,1740]" pageId="6" pageNumber="223" pagination="1 - 48" refId="ref13719" refString="Goodwin, C., Brewin, P. E. &amp; Brickle, P. (2012) Sponge biodiversity of South Georgia Island with descriptions of fifteen new species. Zootaxa, 3542 (1), 1 - 48. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3542.1.1" type="journal article" year="2012">
Goodwin 
<emphasis box="[1094,1149,1713,1739]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="223">et al.</emphasis>
, 2012
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
has similarly small ectosomal tornotes, but these are strongylote, and acanthostyles, albeit exhibiting similar overall dimensions, seemingly cannot be separated in three categories. 
<taxonomicName authority="Salani &amp; Willenz &amp; Fernandez &amp; Hajdu, 2022" authorityName="Salani &amp; Willenz &amp; Fernandez &amp; Hajdu" authorityYear="2022" box="[680,1003,1785,1812]" class="Demospongiae" family="Hymedesmiidae" genus="Hymedesmia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="6" pageNumber="223" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="humboldti" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Hymedesmia">
<emphasis box="[680,825,1785,1811]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="223">Hymedesmia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[843,871,1786,1811]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="223">H.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[889,1003,1785,1811]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="223">humboldti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1012,1104,1786,1812]" pageId="6" pageNumber="223">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1012,1104,1786,1812]" pageId="6" pageNumber="223" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
also bears some similarities, which are further elaborated in its remarks (see below). Other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bowerbank" authorityYear="1864" box="[951,1096,1821,1847]" class="Demospongiae" family="Hymedesmiidae" genus="Hymedesmia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="6" pageNumber="223" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[951,1096,1821,1847]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="223">Hymedesmia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis box="[1111,1138,1822,1847]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="223">H.</emphasis>
) considered here (reported from the Antarctic, Sub-antarctic, SW Atlantic and SE Pacific) possess considerably larger spicules, none has three categories of acanthostyles, and many are only known from the deep sea.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
